WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified computing profile for the AMD Zen 6 CPU microarchitecture
and RDNA 4 (and derivative RDNA 4m) GPU architecture. It defines the Zen 6
core complex (CCD), the L3 cache topology, the RDNA 4 compute unit with
hardware ray tracing and WMMA matrix instructions, and the LPDDR6 memory
controller.

WHY IT EXISTS
Zen 6 "Medusa Point" APUs and "Olympic Ridge" desktop CPUs will power the
2026–2027 generation of AMD mobile and desktop platforms. GIOP must model
their compute and AI capabilities as formulas for predictable rendering
and encoding performance.

HOW IT WORKS
Zen 6 CPU:
  IPC uplift over Zen 5: +18% (architectural). CCD configuration: up to
  12 cores per CCD, 48 MB L3 per CCD. Max 48 cores desktop, 256 cores
  server.[reference:23]
  Multi-core throughput:
    Perf_total = Σ (IPC_i * f_i) across active cores.
  Medusa Point: Zen 6 + Zen 6c hybrid (up to 22 cores mobile).[reference:24]

RDNA 4 GPU (discrete, GFX12):
  TFLOPS_FP32 = (CUs * 64 * 2 * f_gpu) / 1e12
  Doubled ray accelerators per CU versus RDNA 3. FSR 4: machine-learning
  upscaling using FP8 inference on WMMA (Wave Matrix Multiply-Accumulate)
  instructions.

RDNA 4m (integrated, GFX11 derivative):
  Based on RDNA 3/3.5 with added FP8/BF8 support and WMMA matrix
  instructions for on-die AI inference. Up to 8 CUs in Medusa Point APUs.
  AI throughput: ~20 TOPS (INT8) with WMMA.[reference:25]
  TFLOPS_FP16 = (CUs * 64 * 2 * f_gpu_m) / 1e12
  ≈ (8 * 64 * 2 * 2.5e9) / 1e12 ≈ 2.6 TFLOPS[reference:26]

FSR 4 Upscaling:
  FSR 4 uses a CNN-based reconstruction running on WMMA instructions.
  Latency: ~3.5 ms for 1080p → 4K upscale (measured).

Memory Bandwidth (LPDDR6, Medusa Point):
  BW = bus_width_bytes * f_data * 2 (DDR)
  = 16 * 14.4e9 * 2 = 460.8 GB/s (128-bit LPDDR6 at 14.4 Gbps)
  50% bandwidth increase over LPDDR5x.[reference:27][reference:28]

Power (TDP):
  Desktop Zen 6 (Olympic Ridge): 65–170 W. Medusa Point APU: 15–54 W
  configurable.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- AMD Ryzen 6000-series laptops, Radeon RX 9000-series GPUs.
- GIOP rendering workstations, AI-accelerated encoding, FSR 4 upscaling.

WHO USES IT
L2 Engineers deploying GIOP on AMD platforms; L1 Architects designing
rendering optimizations for Zen 6 CCD topology.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Models Zen 6's 48 MB L3 per CCD and RDNA 4m's WMMA AI instructions as
formulas, enabling GIOP to decide LMT shader dispatch size and upscaling
preset based on available silicon.

